description: Handy’s Bistro Crab Cakes are the ideal size and shape for sandwiches. These flavorful crab cakes are crafted with sweet crab meat, scallions, a subtle hint of mustard, and a harmonious blend of herbs and spices. Each crab cake is hand-formed to ensure an authentic, homemade taste. Par-fried for a delightful combination of a crispy exterior and a tender, flavorful crab interior.
cooking_instructions:
The crab cakes contained in this package are par-fried and should be heated thoroughly to 165 °F. Depending on the number of portions prepared and oven temperature variances, heating times may need adjustment. Remove product from packaging. Avoid overcooking or undercooking, cook to a light golden brown.

BAKE: Preheat oven. Spray or coat pan with oil. Place crab cakes on pan and place pan on the middle rack of oven. Turn the crab cakes over once during cooking.

  • FROM THAWED: 375 °F for 10-12 minutes
  • FROM FROZEN: 350 °F for 18-20 minutes

If thawing, thaw under refrigeration or in microwave for 45 seconds on high.

Caution: Pan And Product Will Be Hot.

description: It doesn’t get any better than this! Handy’s Classic Crab Cakes feature generous lumps of sweet fresh crab meat, spices and seasonings for a traditional Maryland-style treat. All Handy crab cakes are gently hand-formed for a true homemade experience.
cooking_instructions:
The crab cakes contained in this package are uncooked and should be cooked until heated through to an internal temperature of 160°F.  Depending on the number of portions prepared and equipment variances, cooking times may require adjustment.

• SUGGESTED COOKING INSTRUCTIONS •
SAUTÉ - Cook in 2 tbsp. of oil on medium heat. Turn cakes over once during cooking.
• 8-10 minutes from thawed  • Cooking from frozen not recommended

BAKE - Preheat oven. Spray or coat pan with oil.  Place pan on rack in middle of oven. Turn cakes over once during cooking. For convection ovens, reduce cooking time by approximately 1/3. 
        • 400°F for 14 - 16 minutes from thawed  
        • 400°F for 24 - 26 minutes from frozen

DEEP FRY - Heat oil to 325°F - 350°F. 
• 5 - 6 minutes from thawed  • Cooking from frozen not recommended

If thawing cakes, thaw under refrigeration or in microwave for 45 seconds on high

• Preparación •
El producto contenido en este paquete no está cocido y debe estar cocinado hasta que este totalmente caliente, a una temperatura interna de 160°F (71°C) antes de consumirlo. Los tiempos de calentamiento pueden variar dependiendo del numero de porciones a preparar y las variaciones de temperatura del microondas.

• Instrucciones de cocina sugeridas •
Sartén - Cocine los pasteles de cangrejo en 2 cucharadas de aceite a fuego medio. Voltee los pasteles una vez durante la cocción.
• 8 - 10 minutos de descongelado
• No se recomienda cocinar congelado
Hornear - Precalentar el horno. Poner producto en una refractaria o una bandeja y colocarlo en el medio del horno. Voltee los pasteles de cangrejo una vez durante la cocción. Para hornos de convección, reduzca el tiempo de cocción por aproximadamente 1/3.
• 400°F (204°C) 14 - 16 minutos de descongelado
• 400°F (204°C) 24 - 26 minutos de congelado
Freír Calentar el aceite hasta llegar a una temperatura de 325°F (163°C) - 350°F (177°C).
• 5 - 6 minutos de descongelado
• No se recomienda cocinar este producto directamente congelado

Al descongelar el producto, descongele bajo refrigeración, o en el microondas a temperatura alta por 45 segundos.  

Note: When preparing our crab cakes, we hand-inspect all crab meat to remove particles of shell.  Despite our close inspection, small particles may occasionally be missed, and it may be possible to find some pieces of shell.
ingredients:

description: Experience the delectable delight of Handy's Crab Cake crafted for the keto-conscious connoisseur. Featuring succulent crab meat, wheat-free ingredients, and perfectly seasoned, our Keto Friendly Crab Cakes are thoughtfully designed without sacrificing taste and texture. With only 2 net carbs per serving, these gluten-free crab cakes offer a guilt-free seafood indulgence. Immerse yourself in a symphony of flavors with our Keto Friendly Crab Cakes!
cooking_instructions:
SUGGESTED COOKING INSTRUCTIONS

The Keto Crab Cakes contained in this package are uncooked and should be cooked thoroughly to 165 °F. Depending on the number of portions prepared and temperature variances, heating times may need adjustment. Remove product from packaging. Avoid overcooking or undercooking, cook to a light golden brown.

BAKE: Preheat oven. Spray or coat pan with oil. Place the crab cakes on pan and place pan on the middle rack of oven. Turn the crab cakes over once during cooking.

  • from thawed: 350°F for 8 minutes, flip and cook for an additional 6 minutes.
  • from frozen: 350°F for 14 minutes, flip and cook for an additional 10 minutes.

SAUTÉ: Cook in 2 tbsp. of oil on medium-low heat.  Turn the crab cakes over once during cooking.

  • FROM THAWED: for 6 minutes, flip and cook for an additional 6 minutes.
  • Cooking from frozen is not recommended.

AIR FRY: Spray basket with oil and place the crab cakes in the basket. Set fryer at 350°F.

  • FROM FROZEN: for 15 minutes. Do not flip during cooking.
  • Cooking from thawed is not recommended.

If thawing, thaw under refrigeration or in microwave for 2 minutes on high.

Caution: Pan and Product Will Be Hot.

description: Handy Seafood’s OLD BAY® Breaded Shrimp features fresh shrimp lightly coated in a crispy OLD BAY panko coating. Oven crispy in a matter of minutes, these easy-to-bake shrimp are perfect for everything from parties to meal planning.
cooking_instructions:
The OLD BAY® Breaded Shrimp contained in this package are precooked and should be cooked thoroughly to an internal temperature of 165°F. Depending on the number of portions prepared andoven temperature variances, heating times may need adjustment. Remove product from packaging. Avoid overcooking or undercooking, cook to a light golden brown.

BAKE

Preheat oven to 425°F. Spray or coat pan with oil.
Place shrimp on pan and place pan on the middle rack of oven.
Turn the shrimp over once during cooking.

  • FROM FROZEN: 425°F for 9 minutes
  • Cooking from thawed is not recommended

AIR FRYER

 Spray or coat the fryer basket with oil and place the shrimp
in basket. Set fryer to 330°F.

  • FROM FROZEN: 330°F for 7 minutes
  • Cooking from thawed is not recommended

TOASTER OVEN

Preheat toaster oven to 400°F. Spray or coat pan with oil.
Place shrimp on pan and place pan on rack in middle of oven.
Turn the shrimp over once during cooking.

  • FROM FROZEN: 400°F for 10 minutes
  • Cooking from thawed is not recommended

Caution: Pan and Product Will Be Hot
When preparing our breaded shrimp, we hand-inspect all shrimp to remove particles of shell. Despite our close inspection, small particles may occasionally be missed, and it may be possible to find some pieces of shell.

cooking_instructions:

BAKE: Preheat oven. Spray or coat pan with oil. Place crab cakes on pan and place pan on the middle rack of oven. Do not turn the crab cakes over during cooking.

MICROWAVE (1000-WATT): Remove crab cake from packaging and place cake on a microwave safe dish. 

• Cooking from thawed is not recommended

• FROM FROZEN: Set microwave at medium power (50% power) and microwave for 4 minutes. 

*when microwaving, you may notice some oil residue on the plate after cooking.

If thawing, thaw under refrigeration or in microwave for 2 minutes on high.

Caution: Pan And Product Will Be Hot.

cooking_instructions:
SUGGESTED COOKING INSTRUCTIONS
The Premium Crab Stuffing contained in this package is ready to cook and should be cooked thoroughly to 165 °F. Remove product from packaging. Natural oil separation may occur—stir gently for a perfect blend. Avoid overcooking or undercooking, cook to a light golden brown. 

OVERNIGHT THAWING: Thaw overnight under refrigeration and use immediately for the best quality and freshness. Keep refrigerated for up to 2 days.

QUICK THAWING: Wrap container in a plastic bag to protect it from water and submerge in cold tap water (78-80 °F) for 2 hours. Use immediately for the best quality and freshness.

Caution: Do not refreeze after thawing. Keep frozen until ready to use.

description: Add fun and variety to your pub dining experience. Handy’s Pub Style Crab Cakes feature fresh crab meat and other seafood, blended with onions and our signature seasonings for a tasty treat. All Handy crab cakes are gently hand-formed for a true homemade experience.
cooking_instructions:
SUGGESTED COOKING INSTRUCTIONS

The Pub Style Crab Cakes contained in this package are ready to cook and should be cooked thoroughly to 165 °F. Depending on the number of portions prepared and temperature variances, heating times may need adjustment. Remove product from packaging. Avoid overcooking or undercooking, cook to a light golden brown.

SAUTÉ: Cook in 2 tbsp. of oil on medium-low heat.  Turn the crab cakes over once during cooking.

  • FROM THAWED: for 8-10 minutes
  • Cooking from frozen is not recommended

 

BAKE: Preheat oven. Spray or coat pan with oil. Place the crab cakes on pan and place pan on the middle rack of oven. Turn the crab cakes over once during cooking.

  • from thawed:  400 °F for 13-15 minutes
  • from frozen: 350 °F for 23-25 minutes

 

DEEP FRY: Heat oil to 350 °F.

  • FROM THAWED: for 3-4 minutes
  • Cooking from frozen is not recommended

If thawing, thaw under refrigeration or in microwave for 2 minutes on high.

Caution: Pan And Product Will Be Hot.

Spanish Cooking Instructions

Los Pub Style Crab Cakes contenidos en este paquete están listos para cocinarse y deben cocinarse hasta que estén totalmente calientes, a una temperatura interna de 165 °F antes de consumirlo. Dependiendo del número de porciones preparadas y variaciones de los equipos, los tiempos de cocción podrán necesitar ajustes. Remover el producto del empaque. Evite la cocción insuficiente o sobre cocinar el producto, cocinar hasta tener un color dorado claro.

 

SAUTÉ: Cocine los pasteles de cangrejo en 2 cucharadas de aceite a fuego medio-bajo. Voltee los pasteles una vez durante la cocción.

  • DESCONGELADO: 8-10 minutos
  • No se recomienda cocinar congelado

 

HORNEAR: Precalentar el horno. Rocíe o cubra bandeja con aceite. Coloque los pasteles de cangrejo en la bandeja y colóquela en el medio del horno. Voltee los pasteles una vez durante la cocción.

  • DESCONGELADO: 400 °F por 13-15 minutos
  • CONGELADO: 350 °F por 23-25 minutos

 

FREIR: Calentar el aceite hasta llegar a una temperatura de 350 °F.

  • DESCONGELADO: 3-4 minutos
  • No se recomienda cocinar congelado

 

Precaución: La bandeja y el producto estarán calientes.

 

Al descongelar el producto, descongele bajo refrigeración, o en el microondas a temperatura alta por 2 minutos.

description: Handy’s Thai Chili Shrimp Rolls feature premium succulent shrimp, accented with sweet chili sauce then hand-wrapped in a delicate pastry sheet.  These crispy mini rolls are perfect as an appetizer and a great addition in seafood platters.
cooking_instructions:
SUGGESTED COOKING INSTRUCTIONS

The Thai Chili Shrimp Rolls contained in this package are par-fried and should be heated thoroughly to 165 °F. Depending on the number of portions prepared and temperature variances, heating times may need adjustment. Remove product from packaging. Avoid overcooking or undercooking, cook to a light golden brown.

 

BAKE: Preheat oven. Spray or coat pan with oil. Place Thai Chili Shrimp Rolls on pan and place pan on the middle rack of oven.

  • from frozen: 350°F for 10-15 minutes
  • Cooking from thawed is not recommended

 

DEEP FRY: Heat oil to 350 °F.

  • FROM FROZEN: for 3-4 minutes
  • Cooking from thawed is not recommended

Caution: Pan And Product Will Be Hot.

Spanish cooking instructions

Los Thai Chili Shrimp Rolls en este paquete están fritos y deben cocinarse hasta que estén totalmente calientes, a una temperatura interna de 165 °F antes de consumirlo. Dependiendo del número de porciones preparadas y variaciones de los equipos, los tiempos de cocción podrán necesitar ajustes. Remover el producto del empaque. Evite la cocción insuficiente o sobre cocinar el producto, cocinar hasta obtener un color dorado claro.

HORNEAR: Precalentar el horno. Rocíe o cubra bandeja con aceite. Coloque los Thai Chili Shrimp Rolls en la bandeja y colóquela en el medio del horno.

  • CONGELADO: 350°F por 10-15 minutos
  • No se recomienda cocinar descongelado

 

FREIR: Calentar el aceite hasta llegar a una temperatura de 350 °F.

  • CONGELADO: 3-4 minutos
  • No se recomienda cocinar descongelado

Precaución: La bandeja y el producto estarán calientes.
ingredients:
